## CSV-only persistence

- All persistence must be in CSV files under `data/`.
- Do not introduce any database, ORM, or external storage system.
- `data/interests.csv` is the source of employee interest submissions.
- Winners must be stored **match-wise** under `data/winners/<matchId>.csv`.
- An employee who appears in any winners file is globally ineligible for other matches (“win once only”).

## Safety

- Prefer rewrite-with-dedupe over append-only when data can be re-submitted (e.g., employee resubmits interest).
- Use a simple in-process lock for CSV writes to avoid corruption.

